# Daily-regenerated DATA artifacts. These are recreated by morning.sh from the network
# + frozen model, so they don't need to live in git and were the main source of noisy
# diffs. They are currently TRACKED — to actually stop the churn, run ONCE on the Mac:
#   git rm --cached data/processed/{results,shootouts,goalscorers,kalshi_wc_contracts,model_vs_market,tournament_probs_live}.parquet \
#                   data/processed/kalshi_wc_contracts.csv data/processed/live_2026_scorecard_log.csv \
#                   data/processed/derived_calibration.json data/raw/results.csv data/raw/goalscorers.csv
# then commit. The FROZEN inputs (poisson_v1.pkl, team_features, calibration.json,
# model_card, training_matrix, elo_*, country_value_history, fair_values_2026,
# simulation_results, tournament_probs) STAY tracked — they are the reproducible state.
data/processed/results.parquet
data/processed/shootouts.parquet
data/processed/goalscorers.parquet
data/processed/kalshi_wc_contracts.parquet
data/processed/kalshi_wc_contracts.csv
